Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray; set aside. Cook turkey bacon according to package directions. Cool slightly and crumble; set aside. Heat turkey sausage according to package directions. Cut into 10 thin slices; set aside. Place Flatout Flatbread on prepared cookie sheet. Bake 2 minutes. Remove from oven. Spread with salsa. Top evenly with cheese, peppers and sausage. Return to oven and bake 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Remove from oven and top with bacon and avocado slices. Drizzle with dressing and serve.